<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 10 SPEED AND 15 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT, RTO, AND RTX
        SERIES - REMOVE - SHIFTING CONTROLS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="14">
        <title>SHIFTING CONTROLS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301513">Figure 13</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301513" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301513" filename="../figg13/G1301513.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Shifting Controls</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Roadranger Valve</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the "P" or End Port of the slave valve on the transmission case (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301514">Figure 14</hotlnk>). Disconnect the air line at the reduction cover
                    (inset).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301514" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301514" filename="../figg13/G1301514.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 14. Disconnect End Port of Slave Valve, and Air Line at Reduction Cover</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the air hose line at the "L" or Low Range Port of the slave valve (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301515">Figure 15</hotlnk>). Disconnect the air line at the "S" or Supply Port
                    (inset).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301515" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301515" filename="../figg13/G1301515.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 15. Disconnect Air Hose Line at Low Range Port of Slave Valve</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If desired, the gear shift lever housing assembly can now be removed from the shifter
                            housing by removing the four bolts from the tower.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two mounting screws in the Roadranger valve cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301516">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301516" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301516" filename="../figg13/G1301516.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 16. Remove Mounting Screws in Roadranger Valve Cover</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the cover down the shift lever to expose the valve ports and disconnect the four
                    air lines (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301517">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301517" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301517" filename="../figg13/G1301517.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 17. Slide Cover Down Shift Lever to Expose Valve Ports</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the jam nut and turn the valve and nut from the gear shift lever (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301518">Figure 18</hotlnk>). Remove the valve cover, air lines, sheathing and
                    O-rings from the lever.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301518" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301518" filename="../figg13/G1301518.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 18. Loosen Jam Nut</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Air Filter/Regulator Assembly</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect and remove the 1/4 inch I.D. air hose between the slave valve (inset,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301519">Figure 19</hotlnk>) and the air filter/regulator assembly.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301519" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301519" filename="../figg13/G1301519.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 19. Disconnect and Remove Air Hose Between Slave Valve and Air Filter/Regulator
                        Assembly
                    </caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two bolts and the air filter/regulator assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301520">Figure 20</hotlnk>). If necessary, remove the two O-rings (inset).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301520" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301520" filename="../figg13/G1301520.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 20. Remove Air Filter/Regulator Assembly</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Slave Valve</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect and remove the 1/4 inch I.D. air hose between the slave valve (inset,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301521">Figure 21</hotlnk>) and the Low Range Port in the housing of the range
                    cylinder.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301521" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301521" filename="../figg13/G1301521.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 21. Disconnect and Remove Air Hose Between Slave Valve and Low Range Port</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect and remove the 1/4 inch I.D. air hose between the slave valve (inset,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301522">Figure 22</hotlnk>) and the High Range Port in the housing of the range
                    cylinder.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301522" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301522" filename="../figg13/G1301522.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 22. Disconnect and Remove Air Hose Between Slave Valve and High Range Port</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolt in the countershaft rear bearing cover to remove the air hoses.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the four bolts, the slave valve and gasket from the transmission case (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301523">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301523" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301523" filename="../figg13/G1301523.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 23. Remove Bolts, Slave Valve and Gasket From Transmission Case</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the hat-type alignment sleeve from the bore in slave valve (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301524">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301524" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301524" filename="../figg13/G1301524.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 24. Remove Hat-Type Alignment Sleeve</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the spring and plunger pin from the bore in the transmission case (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301525">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301525" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301525" filename="../figg13/G1301525.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 25. Remove Spring and Plunger Pin</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If necessary, remove the air hose fittings from the slave valve (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301526">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301526" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301526" filename="../figg13/G1301526.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 26. Remove Air Hose Fittings From Slave Valve</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>For disassembly and reassembly of piston-type Slave Valve Assembly ONLY, see
                            <hotlnk document="s13015_13.xml" xrefid="hl1301505">Slave Valves
                                <xref refid="hl1301505"/>
                            </hotlnk>
                            .
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
